{\color{mediumblue}{\zitiAa\heiti 概况~}}
\zitiA
 热带森林研究中心{--}全球森林监测网络（CTFS-ForestGEO）是科学家们致力于研究热带和温带森林功能和多样性而建成的全球性森林监测样地网络。到2016年，全球森林监测网络横跨美洲、非洲、欧洲、亚洲等区域，在24个国家地区建立了63个大型固定森林监测样地，监测了近10,000个树种、600万棵树木的生长和生存，并且每5年复查一次（图1）。基于全球森林监测网络的数据，超过200名科学家和政策分析者发表了超过1000篇学术论文，其中很多篇发表在《美国科学院学报》《科学》《自然》等顶级学术期刊上，验证了基于该网络研究的这些科学、政策问题的有效性和高影响力（图2）。
 \\[1cm]
{\color{mediumblue}{\zitiAa\phv Overview~}}
The Center for Tropical Forest Science--Forest Global Earth Observatory (CTFS-ForestGEO) is a global network of forest research plots and scientists dedicated to the study of tropical and temperate forest function and diversity. By 2016, the multi-institutional network comprises 63 forest research plots in 24 countries and regions across the Americas, Africa, Europe, and Asia. CTFS-ForestGEO monitors the growth and survival of approximately 6 million trees and 10,000 species, and re-censuses are conducted every 5 years (Figure 1). Based on CTFS-ForestGEO data, over 200 scientists and policy analysts have published over 1,000 scientific articles many in high-profile journals like \emph{the Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences} (US), \emph{Science}, and \emph{Nature}, attesting to the relevance and high impact of the science and policy issues being studied across the network (Figure 2).
